# .vercelignore — minimal exclusions only.
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Replaced 2026-05-21 (claude session 2). Prior version (.vercelignore.bak-2026-05-21)
# was a 15,408-line per-player allowlist that broke whenever player IDs drifted
# between builds. Result: every Heisman -> player link returned 404 on live
# (verified via direct fetch — fernando-mendoza-38276, jeremiyah-love-48316,
# byrum-brown-38981, plus 12 random IDs all 404'd, while Heisman page linked
# to 15,601 of them).
#
# Local check: output/site is 1.3GB with 22,041 files, well within Vercel
# Hobby limits. The historical concern about "Vercel Hobby file-count cap"
# in the prior allowlist comment is not currently binding.
#
# Mirrors tools/write_published_vercelignore.py exclusion set.

# Database files
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Build artifacts
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Dependencies
.deps/
.vendor/
.virtualenv/

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# Temporary files
tmp/
tmp_*/
*.tmp

# Development files
.claude/
.claude-octopus/
.worktrees/
.env
.env.*

# Local box only — these exist on the 24/7 Windows box but never in CI, so the
# cloud .vercelignore never needed them. Without these, a deploy FROM THE BOX
# would try to upload the Python virtualenv (thousands of files) and local
# Vercel/backup dirs. Added 2026-06-08 for the local->Vercel publish path.
.venv/
.vercel.backup/
node_modules/

# Backups
backups/
*.bak
*.backup
.vercelignore.bak-*

# Documentation
CLAUDE*.md
OCTOPUS*.md

# Note: do NOT exclude *.png / *.jpg / *.jpeg here — team logos,
# OG images, and similar assets are PNG/JPG and live under
# assets/team-art/ and assets/. Excluding them broke logo rendering
# on the live site for ~24h (2026-05-14). Use precise paths if any
# specific screenshot needs excluding.

# Test files
tests/
tmp_*.db

# Large source-only directories (not under output/site, but safety)
research/
design-ref/
_fig*/
